Description: Egypt, small group of male and female adults "selling eggs". Two females holding basket and bowl of eggs. Females wearing gowns, head-cloths. Males wearing tunics, turbans. Possibly standing on railway tracks. Rural setting, settlement in distance. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
